### Background

LR35902 has five interrupt sources (VBlank, LCD STAT, Timer, Serial, Joypad) with vectors at fixed addresses in Bank 0. The `IE` (interrupt enable) and `IF` (interrupt flag) registers control which fire. The cooperative scheduler (F-A5.2) uses TIMA's timer interrupt to arm yields; the Bank0 boot module (F-A5.1) wires up the vectors.

